Design System Guidelines — “TVTC Portal Hub” (based on provided screenshots)
Version: 1.1
Audience: Designers + engineers + AI agents generating UI for this project
Goal: Recreate the official, airy TVTC portal look (RTL-first, blue hero overlay, teal/green accents, thin bordered cards) with Arduino-like grid discipline.

============================================================
1) Brand & Creative Direction (the “feel”)
============================================================

Personality
- Institutional but friendly: confident, calm, and clear.
- “Government portal polish”: structured navigation, consistent iconography, restrained color, generous whitespace.
- Visual hierarchy is obvious at a glance; nothing is loud except the primary teal/green accents.

Core design principles
- Clarity beats decoration: large white surfaces, light dividers, one restrained accent family.
- RTL-first composition: right-aligned headlines, navigation, and primary anchors; LTR utility controls are allowed in the top utility bar.
- Layered hero: big photography with a cool blue overlay that keeps text readable.
- Thin-border elegance: cards feel “outlined” more than “shadowed”.
- Consistent rhythm: stable spacing scale, stable card geometry, stable alignment across screens.

============================================================
2) Layout System (structure + grid)
============================================================

Page container
- Max content width: 1200–1280px (Arduino-like content discipline).
- Centered container with responsive side padding:
  - Mobile: 16px
  - Tablet: 24px
  - Desktop: 32px

Grid
- 12-column grid for desktop and tablet.
- Gutter: 24px desktop/tablet, 16px mobile.
- Prefer 3-up or 4-up card grids on desktop; collapse to 2-up on tablet; 1-up on mobile.

Section rhythm (vertical spacing)
- Between major sections: 40–56px desktop, 32–40px tablet, 24–32px mobile.
- Within a section (headline → content): 12–20px.

Alignment rules
- RTL pages: default to right alignment for headings, nav, and body copy.
- Keep baselines aligned: buttons align to text baselines or card bottoms where possible.
- Center alignment is reserved for hero headline blocks and icon-only micro-CTAs.

============================================================
3) Spacing & Sizing Tokens (the rhythm)
============================================================

Spacing scale (use consistently)
- 4, 8, 12, 16, 20, 24, 32, 40, 48, 56, 64

Touch targets
- Minimum interactive size: 44x44px.
- Icon buttons: 40–44px square, with large click area and small icon inside.

Common heights
- Primary buttons: 40–44px
- Inputs/selects: 40–44px
- App header: 64–72px

============================================================
4) Typography (fonts + hierarchy)
============================================================

Type character
- Clean, institutional sans with strong Arabic legibility.
- Prefer simple weights and high contrast; avoid decorative fonts.

Recommended font stack (web)
- Primary (Arabic-first): "Tahoma", "Arial", "Segoe UI", system-ui, sans-serif
- If you choose a modern Arabic webfont, keep it neutral and readable (e.g., "Cairo", "Tajawal") and use it consistently.
- Mono (code snippets only): ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Liberation Mono", "Courier New", monospace

Hierarchy (desktop defaults)
- Display / Hero Title (Arabic): 40–52px, weight 700, line-height 1.1–1.2
- H1: 32–36px, weight 700, line-height 1.15–1.25
- H2: 24–28px, weight 700, line-height 1.2–1.3
- H3: 18–20px, weight 700, line-height 1.25–1.35
- Body: 14–16px, weight 400–500, line-height 1.5–1.7
- Caption/Meta: 12–13px, weight 500, line-height 1.3–1.5

Text style rules
- Headlines: Sentence case or Title Case; keep them short and high-signal.
- Navigation labels: Title Case, medium weight (500–600).
- Primary CTAs: Title Case (preferred). If using ALL CAPS, apply subtle letter spacing (+0.06em) and reduce font size slightly.
- Avoid heavy italics; use weight and color for emphasis.

============================================================
5) Color System (tokens)
============================================================

Design intent
- White, airy surfaces with cool neutrals.
- Primary accents are TVTC-like teal/green + a supporting institutional blue.
- Hero uses a cool blue overlay on photography (signature look from the screenshot).

Core palette (inferred from provided screenshots; tune hex if you have official values)
- Primary (TVTC green/teal family):
  - primary.600 (main):   #008A3E  (deep green used for focus/brand accents in portals)
  - primary.500 (teal):   #18B3A8  (teal used in UI buttons/controls)
  - primary.050 (tint):   #E7F7F5

- Secondary (institutional blue family):
  - secondary.700:        #1F6F8B
  - secondary.600:        #3B7D98
  - secondary.050:        #E9F3F7

- Accent (gold highlight; use sparingly):
  - accent.600:           #F3B200
  - accent.050:           #FFF6D6

- Neutrals:
  - white:              #FFFFFF
  - surface.050:        #F7FAFB
  - surface.100:        #EEF3F5
  - border.200:         #D7E3E8  (cool, slightly blue)

- Text:
  - text.primary:       #0E2A35  (deep blue-gray)
  - text.secondary:     #4F6772
  - text.muted:         #7D929B

- Status (keep quiet; no neon)
  - success:            #2E7D32
  - warning:            #B26A00
  - error:              #C62828
  - info:               #1E88E5

Hero overlay (signature)
- Blue overlay over photography:
  - overlay: rgba(27, 125, 153, 0.55) → rgba(27, 125, 153, 0.75)
  - Keep hero text in white with subtle shadow for legibility.

Color usage rules
- Background is almost always white; use surface.050/100 for subtle panels only.
- Borders are light and cool; avoid strong dark outlines.
- Text uses deep blue-gray, not pure black.
- Primary teal/green is reserved for: CTAs, active states, key links, focus rings.
- Secondary blue is used for: hero overlays, section headers, and institutional emphasis.
- Gold accent is rare: “special” CTA or badge only; never for large surfaces.

============================================================
6) Depth, Borders, and Shape (cards + softness)
============================================================

Radii
- Circular utility buttons: 9999px (true circles)
- Service cards: 12–14px (soft but formal)
- Inputs/selects: 10–12px
- Menus/popovers: 12px

Borders
- Default border: 1px solid border.200
- Service/portal cards: emphasize border (thin teal outline); shadows should be extremely subtle or off.

Shadows (restrained; the screenshot is border-forward)
- Elevation 1 (optional): 0 2px 10px rgba(14, 42, 53, 0.08)
- Elevation 2 (hover):    0 6px 18px rgba(14, 42, 53, 0.12)
- Elevation 3 (overlay):  0 16px 48px rgba(14, 42, 53, 0.18)

Hover lift rule
- Hoverable cards/buttons can lift subtly:
  - translateY(-1px to -2px)
  - shadow increases slightly
  - NEVER jump more than 2px

============================================================
7) Iconography & Illustration
============================================================

Icon style
- Simple, line-based icons with consistent stroke (1.5–2px).
- Rounded line caps, minimal detail.
- Color: text.secondary by default; primary/secondary for active states.

Illustrations/photos
- Use high-quality images with clean backgrounds.
- Crop images to feel editorial (confident framing), not cramped.
- Hero visuals can overlap slightly within a card, but keep padding generous.

============================================================
8) Motion & Interaction
============================================================

Timing
- Micro-interactions: 150–200ms
- Surface transitions / hover: 200–300ms

Easing
- Standard: cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1)
- Hover lift: ease-out

Motion rules
- Keep motion subtle: fade + small translate + soft shadow.
- Respect reduced motion preferences (already present in `web/src/index.css` + `web/src/styles/accessibility.css`).

============================================================
9) Accessibility (non-negotiables)
============================================================

Focus
- Use a clearly visible focus ring with primary green/teal tint:
  - outline: 3px solid primary.600
  - outer glow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(0, 138, 62, 0.25)

Contrast
- Body text must meet WCAG AA.
- Secondary text should remain readable on white; avoid light gray text for important info.

Touch
- Maintain 44px minimum targets (already enforced in accessibility CSS).

============================================================
10) Component Library — High-Level Specs
============================================================

This section defines every component needed for a cohesive design system. Implementations may use any UI framework,
but the visual outcomes must match these rules.

------------------------------------------------------------
10.1 App Shell
------------------------------------------------------------

Header (Two-tier, RTL-first) — matches provided screenshots
- Tier 1 (Utility bar):
  - Height: 48–56px
  - Background: white
  - Layout (RTL): logo lockup on far right; utilities/icons grouped with thin vertical separators
  - Content: accessibility/size toggles, language toggle (EN), account, mail, phone, print, etc. (icons), plus a circular search button
  - Icon style: simple line icons, secondary blue tone
  - Search CTA: circular button, fill primary.500 (teal), icon white
  - Divider: 1px bottom border (border.200)

- Tier 2 (Primary nav):
  - Height: 44–56px
  - Background: white
  - RTL nav links with dropdown carets; consistent spacing between items
  - Hover: shift to secondary.600
  - Active: underline 2px in primary.600/primary.500
  - Keep it flat and clean (no heavy shadows)

Global Container
- Use a centered max-width container; keep header content aligned with page grid.
- Default reading direction: RTL for Arabic screens; align headings and nav to the right.

Hero (Full-bleed carousel) — matches provided screenshots
- Background: full-width photo
- Overlay: cool blue overlay gradient (see “Hero overlay (signature)”)
- Copy block: centered, Arabic headline + one supporting line, all in white
- Carousel dots: centered near hero bottom
  - Inactive: semi-transparent white
  - Active: solid white
- Optional “section header card” overlay near bottom edge: white rounded card with title aligned right and a small emblem icon.

Floating Assist Buttons (Left vertical stack)
- Position: fixed on left side, vertically centered
- Buttons: 3 circular teal buttons (48–56px), icon white
- Hover: subtle brightening only
- Focus: primary focus ring (see accessibility)

------------------------------------------------------------
10.2 Navigation Components
------------------------------------------------------------

Primary Nav Link
- Typography: 14–15px, weight 500–600
- Default: text.primary
- Hover: secondary.600 or text.primary with subtle secondary underline
- Active: primary.600 underline (2px) and slightly stronger weight

Breadcrumbs
- Small, muted, unobtrusive
- Use chevrons; current page in text.primary

Tabs (horizontal)
- Underlined style; active tab uses primary.600 underline
- Tabs sit on white; no heavy backgrounds

Pagination
- Minimal, icon-forward; left/right arrows in circular buttons
- Current page indicated by primary highlight

------------------------------------------------------------
10.3 Buttons
------------------------------------------------------------

Primary Button (Pill CTA)
- Shape: pill (radius 9999)
- Fill: primary.500 (teal) or primary.600 (green) depending on emphasis
- Text: white, weight 600
- Padding: 14–18px horizontal
- Height: 40–44px
- Hover: slightly darker fill, optional 1px lift
- Pressed: darker fill, remove lift

Secondary Button (Pill / Outline)
- Background: white
- Border: 1px solid border.200
- Text: text.primary (or secondary.600 for emphasis)
- Hover: surface.050 background, border slightly darker

Tertiary Button (Link Button)
- No border, no fill
- Text: secondary.600, underline on hover only

Icon Button
- 40–44px square click area
- Icon is 18–22px, centered
- Hover: surface.050 background

------------------------------------------------------------
10.4 Forms & Filters (Search + Select bar)
------------------------------------------------------------

Search Field
- Shape: rounded (10–12px)
- Background: white
- Border: 1px solid border.200
- Placeholder: text.muted
- Leading icon: magnifier in text.muted
- Focus: primary ring (see accessibility)

Select / Dropdown
- Same height and corner radius as inputs
- Caret icon in text.muted
- Menu surface: white, radius 12px, shadow elevation 3
- Menu items: generous vertical padding (10–12px)

Filter Bar Pattern
- Horizontal row: Search field + 2–4 selects
- Spacing: 12–16px between controls
- On mobile: stack vertically with consistent gaps

Checkbox / Radio / Switch
- Minimal and modern; primary.600 for “on/checked”
- Labels: body size 14–15px

------------------------------------------------------------
10.5 Cards & Content Tiles
------------------------------------------------------------

Portal Service Card (Outlined) — matches provided screenshots
- Surface: white
- Radius: 12–14px
- Border: 1.5–2px outline in primary.500 (teal)
- Shadow: none or extremely subtle (border is the separator)
- Layout (centered):
  - Top: emblem/icon inside a soft circular badge (secondary.050 background)
  - Middle: Arabic title (2 lines max), weight 600–700
  - Bottom: rating row (stars) in primary.500 + muted remainder
- Hover: slightly stronger border + subtle lift; keep it calm (no dramatic shadows)

Section Band (Deep teal/blue panel) — matches provided screenshots
- Background: deep teal/blue gradient (secondary.700 → secondary.600)
- Content: right-aligned section title in white + small emblem icon
- Supports an outline button on the left side of the band (white border, white text)
- Cards below the band remain white and airy

------------------------------------------------------------
10.6 Category Navigation (Icon + Label Row)
------------------------------------------------------------

Category Chip/Button
- Visual: icon above label or icon-left label
- Default: text.secondary icon + label
- Active: primary.600 icon + label; optional small underline
- Hit area: at least 56px tall
- Horizontal scroll on small viewports; show subtle left/right affordance

Carousel Controls (Left/Right)
- Circular buttons, border.200
- Hover: surface.050
- Use on white background; keep unobtrusive

------------------------------------------------------------
10.7 Lists, Tables, and Data Display
------------------------------------------------------------

List Item
- White background, subtle divider between items
- Hover: surface.050
- Primary text: weight 600, secondary: muted

Table
- Minimal gridlines: use light borders
- Header: weight 600, text.secondary
- Row hover: surface.050

Badges / Tags / Chips
- Pill shape
- Default: surface.050 background, text.secondary
- Emphasis: primary.050 background with primary.600 text
- Keep small: 24–28px height

------------------------------------------------------------
10.8 Feedback & Status
------------------------------------------------------------

Alert
- Use soft tinted background + subtle border; no screaming saturation
- Icon on left, concise message

Toast / Snackbar
- Dark-ish neutral or white surface with shadow elevation 3
- One clear action max

Progress
- Use primary.600 for progress indication
- Skeletons: neutral shimmer on surface.050, no strong contrast

Empty States
- Friendly illustration/icon + short headline + supporting copy + single CTA
- Keep centered with generous whitespace

------------------------------------------------------------
10.9 Overlays
------------------------------------------------------------

Modal / Dialog
- Radius: 16px
- Background: white
- Shadow: elevation 3
- Header: title left, close icon right
- Actions: primary on the right

Menu / Popover
- Radius: 12px
- Shadow: elevation 3
- Items: 40–44px height, hover surface.050

Drawer (side panel)
- White surface, subtle border, minimal shadow
- Keep spacing consistent with main page container

Tooltip
- Minimal, small radius 8–10px
- Background: text.primary, text: white

------------------------------------------------------------
10.10 Footer
------------------------------------------------------------

Footer Bar
- Background: surface.050 or surface.100
- Thin top border (border.200)
- Left: brand mark
- Right: legal + utility links
- Links: text.secondary, hover primary.600

============================================================
11) Content & Microcopy Style
============================================================

Voice
- Direct, helpful, not cute.
- Prefer short nouns for nav in Arabic (e.g., “الخدمات”, “المنشآت”, “الإدارات”, “تواصل معنا”).
- CTAs use clear verbs (e.g., “عرض”, “استعراض”, “ابدأ”, “جميع الخدمات”).

Formatting
- Avoid long paragraphs; break into scannable lines.
- Use consistent naming: Title Case for sections, sentence case for descriptions.

============================================================
12) Build Notes (framework-agnostic; follow the screenshots)
============================================================

How to implement this look reliably
- Create a small set of tokens (primary/secondary/accent + neutrals + radii + spacing) and use them everywhere.
- Default direction is RTL; only the utility bar may include LTR fragments (like “EN”).
- Keep the header flat with thin dividers; avoid heavy shadows in the top chrome.
- Prefer outlined service cards (teal outline) over shadow-heavy cards.
- Hero must be photo + blue overlay + white centered Arabic headline + dots.

Non-goals
- Do not introduce neon gradients, glassmorphism, or high-contrast dark UI for this style.
- Avoid thick borders, harsh drop shadows, or busy background patterns.

